BABESIOSIS, POSSIBLE - BOSNIA (4)
=================================

Date: Mon, 24 Jun 1996 14:05:11 -0700 (PDT)
From: abenenso@mail.sdsu.edu (A. S. Benenson)
Subject: Babesiosis
Babesiosis was first included in CCDM (Control of Communicable Diseases
in Man) in 1975. The 1995 edition notes that Babesia divergens has been
reported to cause human infections in Yugoslavia as well as in much of
Europe.
